[30;1m71 | [0m[35m``cinder_store_auth_address``, ``cinder_store_user_name``,[0m
[30;1m72 | [0m[35m``cinder_store_project_name``, ``cinder_store_password`` is not set,[0m
[30;1m73 | [0m[35mcinder store uses this information to lookup cinder endpoint from the service[0m
[30;1m74 | [0m[35mcatalog in the current context. ``cinder_os_region_name``, if set, is taken[0m
[30;1m75 | [0m[35minto consideration to fetch the appropriate endpoint.[0m

[30;1m4 | [0m[35m    Previously, during service startup, the check to validate volume types[0m
[30;1m5 | [0m[35m    used to raise ``BackendException`` or ``BadStoreConfiguration`` exceptions[0m
[30;1m6 | [0m[35m    when an invalid volume type was configured hence failing the service[0m
[30;1m7 | [0m[35m    startup. It now logs a warning and the glance service starts normally.[0m
[30;1m8 | [0m[35mfixes:[0m

[30;1m74 | [0m[35mcatalog in the current context. ``cinder_os_region_name``, if set, is taken[0m
[30;1m75 | [0m[35minto consideration to fetch the appropriate endpoint.[0m
[30;1m76 | [0m[35m[0m
[30;1m77 | [0m[35mThe service catalog can be listed by the ``openstack catalog list`` command.[0m
